00:15.098 --> 00:18.601
I came home one day,
and my wife was using heroin.

00:18.977 --> 00:21.021
I fell in love with it pretty quick.

00:22.022 --> 00:24.149
One bag of dope turned into
a gram of dope.

00:24.232 --> 00:26.067
One gram turned into two grams.

00:26.151 --> 00:29.654
The more you do, the more you had to do
to get that same high.

00:30.780 --> 00:33.283
I never expected to live to be 25.

00:33.450 --> 00:34.784
I can't not use.

00:34.868 --> 00:37.120
If I don't use, I'm going to be sick.

00:38.955 --> 00:42.917
I'm 19 years old,
I was up to five Percocets a day.

00:43.293 --> 00:45.253
I didn't have a job.

00:45.712 --> 00:46.880
I was homeless.

00:47.422 --> 00:50.258
I felt like the world didn't need me.

00:51.509 --> 00:54.304
I probably was in high school
the first time I smoked crack.

00:54.846 --> 00:57.390
Did heroin not too long after that.

00:58.224 --> 01:01.269
I'd never really wanted to be in rehab.

01:01.352 --> 01:04.688
Too many of my friends failed over
and over again and family members.

01:06.024 --> 01:07.734
I thought drugs and alcohol...

01:07.817 --> 01:09.402
That's what I grew up around, yeah?

01:09.778 --> 01:11.738
I thought that was just the way
everybody lived.

01:11.821 --> 01:13.448
I didn't know people lived life sober.

01:34.844 --> 01:35.762
Hey, Chad.

01:35.845 --> 01:37.889
-How are you?
-I'm Jeff.

01:38.014 --> 01:39.599
-Meet Jeff.
-Jeff. Chad Bishop.

01:39.682 --> 01:40.767
Nice to meet you.

01:41.226 --> 01:43.019
-Excited?
-Yeah, I'm really excited.

01:43.103 --> 01:44.104
That's good, that's great.

01:45.688 --> 01:48.066
Fired up, man. Number one!

01:48.149 --> 01:49.442
Number one!

01:49.526 --> 01:51.069
How's it going?

01:51.194 --> 01:52.904
You guys got anything to carry in?

01:52.987 --> 01:55.573
No, he's got everything he's got
right there in his hands.

01:55.657 --> 01:58.076
- All right. All right.
- Nice place.

01:58.743 --> 02:01.663
We were still working on it
when we opened up.

02:01.746 --> 02:05.625
-Wow. Nice.
-Same bathroom, same way.

02:05.708 --> 02:06.668
This is yours.

02:07.544 --> 02:09.044
-This is mine.
-Which bed do you want?

02:10.755 --> 02:12.757
-This one.
-All right.

02:13.508 --> 02:15.635
You should see the mat I was sleeping on.

02:15.718 --> 02:16.719
I know the feeling.

02:16.803 --> 02:18.304
It's like sleeping on a towel.

02:19.180 --> 02:22.100
Yeah, these are comfortable beds.
Try it out.

02:22.183 --> 02:23.601
Yeah, man, this is awesome.

02:24.519 --> 02:28.565
He had his court hearing yesterday
for his girls,

02:28.648 --> 02:30.191
and because he was coming up here,

02:30.316 --> 02:32.569
they extended his period,

02:32.652 --> 02:35.280
so they didn't take his girls away
from him yet, so...

02:35.405 --> 02:37.699
-That's good.
-How old are they now? One and three?

02:37.782 --> 02:39.325
-Two and three.
-Okay.

02:39.409 --> 02:42.495
-How long have you been married?
-Since I was 20.

02:42.579 --> 02:43.955
Really? You're 25?

02:44.038 --> 02:45.665
-In June, I turn 26.
-Twenty-six?

02:46.499 --> 02:49.127
-No gang affiliations, anything like that?
-No.

02:49.502 --> 02:50.587
Very good.

02:50.670 --> 02:53.631
Tomorrow basically,
we'll wake you up, get you fed,

02:53.715 --> 02:56.634
and then we're going to go over
to the farm and feed the animals,

02:56.718 --> 02:58.386
do a little bit of work over there.

02:58.970 --> 03:01.931
Evening time, around six, seven o'clock,

03:02.432 --> 03:06.728
that would be some of your time
for educational classes.

03:07.020 --> 03:11.065
You've been here about 45 minutes.
You're officially our senior resident.

03:12.942 --> 03:14.652
- It's a lot of responsibility.
- Yeah!

03:15.320 --> 03:17.071
- Here I am, that's me.
- You're it.

03:35.131 --> 03:38.176
I mean, if that doesn't give you
a new perspective,

03:38.259 --> 03:39.427
I don't know what will.

03:53.274 --> 03:57.320
The guys won't have a lot
of outside world contact,

03:57.654 --> 03:59.280
unless it's supervised.

04:00.740 --> 04:03.618
You really want to kind of keep the guys
from isolating,

04:03.701 --> 04:05.995
because that's kind of
where their life's been.

04:06.537 --> 04:08.081
It's been them and their drug.

04:09.540 --> 04:14.671
Farming life is a series of advances
and a couple of setbacks,

04:14.754 --> 04:19.926
and they'll be able to experience
that kind of stuff sober.

04:20.510 --> 04:23.554
Life's not always going to be perfect,
it's not always going to be good,

04:23.680 --> 04:26.516
and you have to learn to live
with pain and setbacks,

04:27.016 --> 04:30.103
without having drugs to dampen it for you.

04:32.814 --> 04:33.731
Morning, guys.

04:33.815 --> 04:35.483
-Morning, Mark.
-How are you doing?

04:35.608 --> 04:36.859
Fantastic.

04:37.068 --> 04:39.445
You ever worked with animals before?
Have you?

04:39.529 --> 04:42.198
-Yeah, my papa had a little farm.
-A farm? Okay.

04:49.706 --> 04:52.083
These are the ones
that are gonna go out on pasture.

04:52.709 --> 04:54.836
You can just stick it in front of him.

04:55.503 --> 04:57.130
He should at least for a while.

04:57.630 --> 04:58.881
Tip it up. There you go.

04:58.965 --> 05:00.800
- You look like you've done it.
- Yeah.

05:00.883 --> 05:01.718
Okay.

05:03.136 --> 05:05.722
This is my brother Benny.

05:06.514 --> 05:09.225
He's on heroin and meth real bad
right now.

05:09.726 --> 05:13.187
That's Aaron, my mom's boyfriend John,
the one she's married to now.

05:13.521 --> 05:15.648
That's his son that ODed.

05:16.733 --> 05:18.818
He's passed away,
and that's my brother AJ.

05:19.527 --> 05:21.195
Which is locked up in prison

05:21.821 --> 05:25.283
for robbing Hardee's
in Sabraton, Morgantown,

05:25.783 --> 05:26.993
to get drugs and stuff.

05:29.746 --> 05:30.872
That's my sister,

05:31.164 --> 05:33.541
my mom and her two kids,

05:33.624 --> 05:35.293
but she don't have nothing
to do with them.

05:35.376 --> 05:37.837
She's on the run from the law right now.

05:38.838 --> 05:40.465
And my mom has both kids.

05:42.175 --> 05:43.009
These are cute.

05:44.010 --> 05:44.844
That's my kid.

05:45.845 --> 05:48.014
That's her when she just started walking.

05:57.023 --> 05:59.150
Got a lot of amends to make
to a lot of these people,

05:59.233 --> 06:00.735
but I don't know who they are.

06:02.236 --> 06:04.030
I've broken into a lot of these houses.

06:04.113 --> 06:06.991
I've gone through... in my addiction.

06:10.119 --> 06:13.539
- There's some amends you just can't make.
- There are some.

06:15.625 --> 06:18.920
Some of them, maybe you could write
a letter, put it in their mailbox.

06:19.587 --> 06:22.757
'Cause it would be risky knocking
on the door, some of them,

06:22.840 --> 06:26.386
telling them what you did,
they may not take too kindly to it.

06:28.054 --> 06:30.848
Especially in these parts,
people tend to carry guns with them.

06:30.932 --> 06:32.767
Yeah, they'll shoot you around here.

06:36.562 --> 06:38.314
See that church
way over on that hill?

06:38.398 --> 06:40.358
- Yeah.
- That's where my real dad's buried.

06:40.441 --> 06:41.442
- Really?
- Yeah.

06:42.402 --> 06:46.072
-Did you ever know him?
-No, I was three when he passed away.

06:46.614 --> 06:48.616
-That's when my mom left.
-What happened?

06:48.866 --> 06:50.493
A tree got cut down on Papa.

06:50.576 --> 06:51.577
-Really?
-Yeah.

06:51.661 --> 06:53.579
-Wow.
-At a logging yard.

06:56.833 --> 07:01.003
Then a year later, my mom left,
went to a bar and never came home.

07:02.338 --> 07:05.800
-So she left when you were three?
-Three years old, yeah.

07:05.883 --> 07:07.802
And didn't come back until I was 15 or 16.

07:07.885 --> 07:09.929
Jeez! Where'd she go?

07:10.012 --> 07:10.888
I don't know.

07:27.363 --> 07:29.866
I like to sit here sometimes quietly.

07:30.700 --> 07:32.535
Like, when you're, like, high and stuff,

07:32.618 --> 07:34.454
you don't really think about what...

07:35.329 --> 07:36.914
You know what I mean? You ain't got...

07:36.998 --> 07:38.666
I wake up, my first thing is,

07:38.833 --> 07:40.710
I gotta find my needle
and go find me some dope.

07:40.793 --> 07:41.752
You know what I mean?

07:42.253 --> 07:43.713
But now that you're not high,

07:43.796 --> 07:46.591
you come out here in the morning,
you listen to all the birds.

07:46.674 --> 07:49.093
When you're high,
you don't focus on shit like that.

07:49.677 --> 07:52.221
I hear a bird over here right now.
You know what I mean?

07:52.305 --> 07:53.764
And you can hear some over here.

07:54.348 --> 07:56.767
When they go together, it's like...
You know what I mean?

07:57.477 --> 07:59.145
You appreciate the little things in life.

07:59.228 --> 08:01.022
Yeah, you do, but when you're high,

08:01.105 --> 08:03.024
you really don't focus
on no shit like that.

08:03.107 --> 08:05.651
-You see through it.
-Yeah, I agree.

08:06.068 --> 08:06.903
Beautiful.

08:07.778 --> 08:10.072
Let's go. Let's go!

08:12.533 --> 08:14.619
And instead of posting,
see if it wedges.

08:14.702 --> 08:16.913
If it wedges,
don't take it all the way out.

08:17.246 --> 08:18.789
-Minimalistic.
-Yes.

08:22.001 --> 08:24.670
Long story short,
I've been a drug addict since I was 16,

08:24.754 --> 08:27.381
and in and out of programs.
This is my tenth program.

08:28.132 --> 08:32.178
And I came to Jacob's Ladder. I was
at a wilderness program before this.

08:32.886 --> 08:37.058
And my mom found it for me,
and you know,

08:37.140 --> 08:40.102
I've never been on a recovery place
like this where it's on a farm.

08:42.938 --> 08:44.190
I know what people want to hear,

08:44.273 --> 08:47.777
so it's really easy for me
to skate through a program undetected.

08:47.860 --> 08:50.238
You know, they say,
"This kid is really doing good."

08:50.363 --> 08:51.781
Really, I was bullshitting my way,

08:51.864 --> 08:53.783
waiting to get out,
on the outside, to use.

08:53.908 --> 08:56.077
Deep down I really wanna be sober.
I don't wanna die.

08:56.410 --> 08:59.455
Nobody really wants to die.
Even a normal human doesn't wanna die.

09:00.248 --> 09:01.374
I don't know, I'm just...

09:02.542 --> 09:05.253
I'm really excited
to actually give it 100%,

09:05.753 --> 09:07.547
'cause I've never done that before.

09:07.964 --> 09:09.340
I've never given it my all.

09:38.286 --> 09:40.496
-Craig, addict.
-Hi, Craig.

09:40.580 --> 09:44.000
So what I wanna do next
is we're gonna go around,

09:44.083 --> 09:46.502
we're gonna check in,
how your week's going,

09:46.586 --> 09:48.546
what's the struggle,
what's going well for you.

09:49.213 --> 09:51.882
-I'm Adam, and I'm an addict.
-Hey, Adam.

09:52.633 --> 09:55.136
Yeah, you know,
this week's been up and down.

09:56.387 --> 09:58.931
I got, you know,
the first letter from my grandma.

10:00.433 --> 10:03.811
She... She's, like,
the center of my addiction.

10:03.894 --> 10:07.273
You know, that was, like,
where I got all my money.

10:07.356 --> 10:09.275
You know, if I needed something,
I ran there,

10:09.358 --> 10:12.486
and either she gave it to me,
or most of the time,

10:12.570 --> 10:15.990
I just conned her out of it one way
or another, to put it blatantly.

10:17.533 --> 10:19.535
She sent me this letter and she said,

10:20.119 --> 10:22.955
"I forgive you. I couldn't be mad at you.

10:23.039 --> 10:24.707
I love you," and all this,

10:24.790 --> 10:26.334
and I was just thinking, like,

10:26.417 --> 10:29.211
"I took a significant amount of money
from this woman."

10:29.295 --> 10:31.797
I mean, I ruined her life in my eyes.

10:31.881 --> 10:33.007
I mean, she's 86,

10:33.549 --> 10:37.595
and she's working at the Goodwill,
so that she is not homeless right now.

10:38.012 --> 10:40.556
Myself, I couldn't just forgive
someone like that.

10:40.640 --> 10:42.224
I don't care who they are.

10:42.308 --> 10:44.727
I don't deserve
the forgiveness that I got,

10:44.810 --> 10:47.647
that quickly and out of nowhere.

10:48.439 --> 10:49.899
I just don't know what to do.

10:50.733 --> 10:52.193
That make sense to you guys?

10:52.276 --> 10:53.152
Yeah, dude.

11:26.227 --> 11:27.687
Don't run, you guys.

11:28.771 --> 11:29.772
I almost ran.

11:30.231 --> 11:31.065
Thank you.

11:31.440 --> 11:33.234
You saved my life many a time.

11:33.984 --> 11:35.486
You have no idea how true that is.

11:35.778 --> 11:38.114
Fourteen times I've overdosed, guys.

11:38.197 --> 11:39.323
Fourteen times.

11:52.128 --> 11:55.798
Dude, I busted my shin on that rope.

11:59.719 --> 12:00.720
Oh!

12:35.713 --> 12:37.923
Chad told me we were going for a hayride.

12:38.716 --> 12:40.426
This ain't what I had in mind.

12:40.801 --> 12:42.178
Yeah, I know.

12:47.224 --> 12:48.601
These are peppers here.

12:48.684 --> 12:50.436
You can tell in the leaves.

12:50.519 --> 12:51.353
Yep.

12:52.313 --> 12:54.398
I feel like if we're flexible...

12:56.317 --> 12:57.735
and we're compassionate,

12:58.819 --> 13:03.157
then, I mean, that to me is the best
combination of trying to help people.

13:03.741 --> 13:05.993
I mean, if you lose either one
of those two qualities,

13:06.076 --> 13:07.745
I think you're really hamstrung.

13:08.329 --> 13:09.747
No matter what you're doing,

13:09.830 --> 13:13.292
if you're giving these guys a place
to be surrounded by good people,

13:13.375 --> 13:15.461
I mean, they're way ahead
of the game already.

13:25.137 --> 13:27.681
Jake and Jerrica, his older sister,

13:27.765 --> 13:30.559
in the Bahamas, we went conch diving.

13:31.519 --> 13:34.814
Jake was probably withdrawing
in this picture.

13:34.897 --> 13:38.192
-I was, yeah.
-I didn't know at the time, but he was...

13:38.734 --> 13:41.445
-I thought you knew. You said...
-Did I know then, in this one?

13:41.529 --> 13:43.364
-You had a hunch.
-Yeah.

13:44.448 --> 13:46.784
I can't remember,
but look how skinny he is.

13:48.077 --> 13:48.911
Pretty skinny.

13:49.662 --> 13:51.705
-I got worse than that, though.
-Yeah.

13:52.790 --> 13:54.375
'Cause I was more interested in pills.

13:54.959 --> 13:58.796
I think I, like, snuck one Oxy with me.

13:59.171 --> 14:00.673
-Did you?
-Uh-huh.

14:01.340 --> 14:04.218
Looking pretty... pretty strung out.

14:04.718 --> 14:06.345
-That's 'cause I was, yeah.
-Yeah.

14:16.564 --> 14:18.399
Everything's hurting.

14:19.650 --> 14:21.652
Arm and legs a little bit higher.

14:25.656 --> 14:27.783
How did your court date go last week?

14:27.867 --> 14:28.826
Oh, man.

14:29.243 --> 14:30.286
Not good?

14:32.204 --> 14:36.292
The court date went good,
but I got some bad news about my daughter.

14:37.543 --> 14:39.461
Put me in a bad mood all week.

14:40.421 --> 14:42.214
My daughter went to a foster home.

14:42.298 --> 14:44.592
While she was in there, they molested her.

14:44.717 --> 14:48.012
And I just found out about it,
so we're in the middle of that.

14:48.095 --> 14:50.764
It's being investigated right now
and stuff.

14:51.515 --> 14:53.225
You know what I mean?
It's been a bad week.

14:55.436 --> 14:58.522
Jeff, you got quiet,
brother. What are you thinking?

14:59.273 --> 15:00.149
What do you mean?

15:00.649 --> 15:02.568
You're not quiet usually,
so what's going on?

15:02.651 --> 15:04.153
-I'm just kicking it, dude.
-Huh?

15:04.236 --> 15:05.696
Just kicking it, listening.

15:06.530 --> 15:09.992
What went on for you when I brought up
stuff in your life right now, then?

15:10.701 --> 15:13.203
I don't know. I keep telling myself
all day today,

15:13.287 --> 15:14.788
if I wouldn't have picked up and used,

15:15.581 --> 15:17.708
you know what I mean,
if I wouldn't have got caught,

15:18.459 --> 15:21.587
they would never have got taken,
she would never have got molested.

15:21.670 --> 15:22.880
Do you know what I mean?

15:23.255 --> 15:26.926
I feel like my actions led
to that shit, man.

15:28.844 --> 15:31.347
-I just want to kill the dude.
-I get it, man.

15:33.390 --> 15:36.185
One thing's on my shoulder
saying I'm doing the right thing,

15:36.268 --> 15:38.395
stay here, and it'll all work out.

15:38.938 --> 15:41.774
Let the cops,
let the law take care of it and stuff,

15:42.024 --> 15:43.651
and another part of my shoulder's like,

15:43.734 --> 15:46.278
"Man, step the fuck up.
Kill this motherfucker."

15:46.362 --> 15:47.446
You know what I mean?

15:48.280 --> 15:49.657
Protect your daughter.

15:52.117 --> 15:54.328
I'm just lost.
I don't know what to do, man.

15:54.912 --> 15:56.330
I just don't wanna go there.

15:57.247 --> 16:00.209
A part of me wants to stay, too,
so I'm just... I'm lost.

16:00.292 --> 16:02.461
I just... I don't know what to do.

16:06.423 --> 16:08.217
I don't fucking know, man.

16:10.094 --> 16:10.970
I don't know.

16:14.640 --> 16:15.557
Well, what...

16:16.517 --> 16:20.479
You're doing it right now though, right?
You're talking, coming out with it.

16:20.562 --> 16:24.525
'Cause it's obvious that all this stuff
is sitting in you, in your head.

16:24.650 --> 16:28.153
You're the one that thinks you get away
with it with all the jokey shit,

16:28.237 --> 16:31.365
but it's obvious you can't have
something like that pop into your life,

16:31.448 --> 16:33.325
and then it just evaporates.

16:33.409 --> 16:34.702
It ain't gonna go away.

16:34.785 --> 16:36.829
So here we got your brothers
here in recovery,

16:36.912 --> 16:38.247
and this is to you guys, right?

16:38.330 --> 16:40.916
You know this is your guy,
he's struggling,

16:41.041 --> 16:43.752
so are we just talking shit every day?

16:44.044 --> 16:45.212
Are we just having fun?

16:45.629 --> 16:48.966
But he's struggling, right?
Now you see on his face.

16:49.299 --> 16:51.260
So what are we doing to support Jeff?

16:51.343 --> 16:52.344
We've all seen it.

16:52.970 --> 16:55.764
It sucks because I've been there too,
and I've gone out over it...

16:56.348 --> 17:00.185
and I came back, like,
I've had a lot of survivor's guilt,

17:00.269 --> 17:02.563
and you know,
I've seen a lot of my friends die.

17:02.646 --> 17:04.772
You've seen your daughter go through
some tough things.

17:04.857 --> 17:07.151
I've got my daughter taken away from me
because of heroin.

17:07.233 --> 17:10.194
I mean, it's gonna sound really harsh,
but you need to be selfish,

17:10.279 --> 17:12.321
because what do you have
to offer to your daughter

17:12.406 --> 17:14.532
versus the world right now?
Absolutely nothing.

17:15.200 --> 17:16.952
Until you get right with yourself.

17:18.829 --> 17:20.664
I failed big time, you know?

17:21.957 --> 17:23.333
She's three years old, man.

17:26.045 --> 17:27.546
And already got fucked with.

17:28.756 --> 17:30.090
I'm supposed to stop that.

17:36.555 --> 17:37.806
I can't do this no more.

17:44.521 --> 17:45.856
Get him up there.

17:48.942 --> 17:52.154
I'm curious to ask
how you guys are feeling right now.

17:52.237 --> 17:55.699
I've been in that exact situation.
Not exactly, like, I've...

17:56.533 --> 17:58.327
I got to the point
where I wanted to leave,

17:58.410 --> 18:00.621
but I wanted to stay
and I ended up leaving.

18:00.704 --> 18:04.124
I ended up relapsing,
ODed another four times, you know?

18:04.208 --> 18:06.335
Yeah, but was it because of that reason?

18:06.418 --> 18:08.170
-Not exactly.
-That your child was molested?

18:08.253 --> 18:10.422
-No, but I've been raped.
-That takes a toll on someone.

18:10.506 --> 18:13.008
I was raped when I was six years old,
so I feel the situation.

18:13.092 --> 18:14.802
We should not compare war stories,
brother.

