Yeah!

37:45.221 --> 37:47.682
I'll go up there.
I need someone to make me dance.

37:48.849 --> 37:50.559
-Feel out of place, don't you?
-Yeah, I do.

37:50.643 --> 37:53.646
Yeah, but you gotta challenge it
'cause you're not out of place, dude.

37:54.855 --> 37:56.315
We need people on the floor.

37:56.399 --> 37:58.818
This is a very simple, simple dance.

37:59.235 --> 38:00.569
Just pick a partner.

38:02.697 --> 38:05.116
-Come on, dude. Go.
-Go ahead, Ryan.

38:05.199 --> 38:07.243
-There you go.
-I'm Ryan.

38:07.994 --> 38:08.953
Nice to meet you.

38:09.829 --> 38:11.664
-I'm Rush.
-I'm Debbie.

38:11.747 --> 38:13.207
-Nice to meet you, Debbie.
-You, too.

38:15.126 --> 38:16.961
Son, just go pick a partner.

38:17.837 --> 38:19.714
This is it, you guys. Come on up!

38:19.797 --> 38:22.383
There are some ladies here
that need someone. Come on.

38:24.677 --> 38:26.971
Now join your hands and circle out.

38:32.310 --> 38:33.811
Now back to the right.

38:38.441 --> 38:40.526
Swing your honey once around.

38:43.195 --> 38:44.655
And promenade.

38:46.032 --> 38:46.907
Okay, all four.

38:49.201 --> 38:50.077
Well, whatever!

38:55.750 --> 38:58.002
Couple number one, out to the right.

38:58.794 --> 38:59.754
Go right on.

39:01.839 --> 39:03.549
Jeff, you're causing major confusion.

39:06.385 --> 39:08.387
This is the most fun I've had
in a long time.

39:21.025 --> 39:23.819
I want to thank you guys
for dancing. You can go and sit down.

39:38.376 --> 39:40.044
When do you want this place ready by?

39:40.920 --> 39:41.921
Couple weeks.

39:42.922 --> 39:45.049
Yeah.

39:46.425 --> 39:48.844
Honestly though,
even if it was a sober house,

39:48.928 --> 39:51.639
and we were still working on it
while we lived here, it wouldn't be...

39:51.722 --> 39:54.058
Jorge is getting the kitchen done...

39:54.141 --> 39:57.436
Everyone wants to stay in this area
when they finish Jacob's Ladder,

39:57.561 --> 40:00.648
and so we purchased a property,
we're finishing it up,

40:00.731 --> 40:03.818
so that it can be a sober living setting
for these guys.

40:04.527 --> 40:07.571
If they can get jobs in the community
and they want to stay here,

40:07.655 --> 40:10.491
that keeps them connected
to what they're doing already.

40:11.826 --> 40:13.160
-Are you tired?
-Yes.

40:13.244 --> 40:14.703
-You've been scraping?
-A lot.

40:14.787 --> 40:18.707
I worry every day about these guys
leaving here and going back home,

40:19.125 --> 40:21.335
getting back to the playground
and to the friends

40:21.419 --> 40:23.796
and all the things
that they used to get into.

40:24.422 --> 40:26.340
When they're here,
there's a little vacation

40:26.424 --> 40:29.927
from all the chaos of their lives
that they got themselves into,

40:30.010 --> 40:32.012
and they're gonna go back
to the real world.

40:32.096 --> 40:33.639
We're trying to get them ready for it.

40:34.306 --> 40:36.600
It's a great start here,
that's what it is.

40:36.684 --> 40:40.146
I mean, nothing's promised
when a guy leaves our program.

40:40.855 --> 40:43.065
- I'm an addict named Jeff.
- Jeff.

40:43.149 --> 40:44.859
I'm a father of two girls,

40:44.942 --> 40:48.070
and my addiction took over
a good person

40:48.737 --> 40:52.783
and turned me into a   monster, I can say.

40:54.243 --> 40:56.162
And I didn't care who I hurt, man.

40:56.287 --> 40:57.955
I didn't care what I had to do.

40:58.539 --> 41:00.249
Tearing families apart,

41:00.833 --> 41:02.543
ruining lives, man.

41:06.839 --> 41:10.968
I want that new way of life.
I remember every day when I wake up.

41:11.093 --> 41:13.846
Just don't use today, no matter what.
Don't pick up.

41:15.014 --> 41:18.142
But that's all I grew up around, you know?
That's all I know.

41:18.517 --> 41:22.104
It's all my family does,
it's all my friends do.

41:22.521 --> 41:24.940
Basically, my whole town does it,
you know?

41:25.107 --> 41:25.941
And that's...

41:26.400 --> 41:28.611
I don't know a sober person back home.

41:29.528 --> 41:31.363
It kind of scares me, you know?

41:35.743 --> 41:36.619
Yeah, that's all.

41:36.994 --> 41:39.371
- Thanks, Jeff.
- Thanks. I really appreciate that.

41:41.916 --> 41:43.876
Come on, man.
Teamwork makes the dream work.

41:43.959 --> 41:44.960
There we go.

41:45.044 --> 41:47.171
-Teamwork makes the dream work?
-It did.

41:47.254 --> 41:51.425
I picked Jeff up
six months ago down at the regional jail.

41:51.842 --> 41:53.844
He came running around the corner

41:54.220 --> 41:57.181
with all his worldly possessions
in his hands,

41:57.264 --> 41:59.099
and he looked at me.
He'd never met me before,

41:59.183 --> 42:01.810
and he said, "Let's get out of here
before they change their mind."

42:05.397 --> 42:07.399
Man, I call Jeff "old dad."

42:11.612 --> 42:13.364
Yeah, he's younger than me,

42:14.532 --> 42:15.908
but he's got the wisdom...

42:18.619 --> 42:19.537
...that I needed.

42:20.246 --> 42:23.666
I'm glad he's sticking around
'cause I love this guy, I really do.

42:24.041 --> 42:26.502
Yeah. It's hard not to get emotional.

42:27.294 --> 42:31.257
I'm really gonna miss this place.
I wanna say thanks to you, Dr. B.

42:31.674 --> 42:35.678
You heard me out, listened to my story
and you took me in and gave me a chance.

42:37.846 --> 42:39.515
-Thanks, man.
-I love you, buddy.

42:41.976 --> 42:43.310
- I love you.
- Me too.

42:58.534 --> 43:00.494
I wanna thank everybody for coming out,

43:00.578 --> 43:03.247
helping us celebrate
Adam's graduation.

43:06.041 --> 43:07.626
I'm Leslie. I'm Adam's mom.

43:08.794 --> 43:10.713
It's been a long few years for us.

43:11.547 --> 43:12.840
I am so proud of you,

43:13.299 --> 43:16.760
and all the hard work that you put
into yourself is really paying off,

43:17.636 --> 43:19.138
and I could not be more proud.

43:20.431 --> 43:21.974
I just love you to death.

43:32.568 --> 43:35.362
I'm really not good
with speeches, guys, but...

43:42.745 --> 43:44.705
It's been a long road, man.

43:50.252 --> 43:51.879
It's been a long road.

43:54.214 --> 43:56.675
I've learned what a friend is, you know?

43:58.719 --> 44:00.471
'Cause I didn't know,

44:00.929 --> 44:04.767
and now I have more than I can count
on both of my hands.

44:51.438 --> 44:52.856
Jeff, wake up.

44:53.482 --> 44:55.734
Come on, it's time to drive.

44:55.984 --> 44:56.819
I'm ready.

45:06.912 --> 45:09.998
Not allowed to play rap
once you get to the coal mine.

45:10.082 --> 45:11.375
But we don't give a fuck.

45:54.251 --> 45:56.628
I had some depression the last two days.

45:57.421 --> 45:59.840
Just, I don't know.
I don't know what it was.

46:00.132 --> 46:01.842
Just was down.

46:01.925 --> 46:02.760
"Woe is me."

46:03.761 --> 46:05.387
Obviously it's still under construction.

46:05.471 --> 46:08.265
You know, it's not like
we have the most fun here.

46:12.811 --> 46:15.689
I hung out with that girl last night.
She's fucking weird.

46:16.982 --> 46:17.983
You know, tight.

46:19.985 --> 46:21.528
-Never again.
-Never again.

46:26.533 --> 46:27.659
It's boring up here.

46:28.911 --> 46:29.870
Really boring.

46:33.290 --> 46:36.710
I get up at four o'clock every morning,
take Adam to work.

46:37.419 --> 46:39.379
Pick him up at four o'clock
in the evening.

46:40.005 --> 46:43.842
Go on a couple of dates here and there,
eat out a lot, that's all I do.

46:44.635 --> 46:46.136
I work for that guy, Scott,

46:46.220 --> 46:48.680
and he fucking was smoking weed
in front of me.

46:49.014 --> 46:51.266
It didn't bother me
that he was smoking weed.

46:51.642 --> 46:54.937
Weed ain't my thing anyways.
Drinking ain't my thing.

46:55.270 --> 46:57.731
But if there was a gram of dope,
it probably would have been...

46:57.856 --> 47:00.484
If he was sitting there banging some dope,
I'd probably be like...

47:00.567 --> 47:02.236
You know what I mean?

47:02.694 --> 47:05.322
My thing is when I get in the truck
or the car,

47:06.240 --> 47:07.783
and I put on some music...

47:08.242 --> 47:10.410
You know what I mean?
Just driving down the road.

47:11.328 --> 47:13.622
I feel like I need to smoke a fat blunt.

47:14.164 --> 47:15.624
'Cause that's just what I do.

47:36.603 --> 47:38.438
Thanks, everybody, for coming out.

47:38.730 --> 47:42.985
It's a special day, and this is a special
resident that we're graduating today.

47:43.318 --> 47:46.363
If every program has to have a heart,
that's Ryan.

47:46.446 --> 47:47.990
Ryan's the heart of this program.

47:48.615 --> 47:50.909
Ryan, if there's anything
you'd like to say to the folks...

47:51.743 --> 47:55.998
I turn everything into the topic
of gratitude.

47:56.540 --> 47:57.374
Okay?

47:59.501 --> 48:01.712
Every day of my life,
I'm going to continue

48:02.296 --> 48:05.340
to show you gratitude,

48:05.674 --> 48:07.134
Jacob's Ladder gratitude.

48:07.843 --> 48:09.595
I just love everyone

48:10.429 --> 48:13.515
that has anything to do
with helping people

48:13.599 --> 48:16.685
that everybody else in society
looks down on.

48:17.269 --> 48:20.355
And just... it's amazing.

48:20.731 --> 48:22.649
It's really incredible,

48:22.733 --> 48:25.652
and there is not a lot of places
like this on the planet.

48:26.153 --> 48:28.113
This is a special fucking place.

48:28.780 --> 48:32.034
Everyone that comes here
has an opportunity

48:33.243 --> 48:34.912
that a lot of people don't get.

48:35.454 --> 48:37.372
Someone out there is dying right now.

48:38.540 --> 48:39.374
You know?

48:40.125 --> 48:41.126
It's horrible.

48:41.835 --> 48:43.337
It's gonna keep happening,

48:44.046 --> 48:47.841
but we don't have to be part
of the problem anymore.

48:48.592 --> 48:50.177
You know? We don't.

48:51.011 --> 48:54.514
Like, this is it. This is life today.

48:55.140 --> 48:56.683
And that's all we got.

49:06.610 --> 49:09.488
My keys right there, you hear that?

49:09.571 --> 49:13.450
Ooh, sounds nice.

49:14.117 --> 49:17.287
I think it's this door right here.

49:18.497 --> 49:20.707
I think the counter space is nice, man.

49:21.124 --> 49:23.794
You got a washer and dryer, too.
It's got a laundry chute.

49:25.921 --> 49:26.922
Yeah, we're good.

49:27.130 --> 49:29.841
We're good. No one left a bottle
of Vicodin in here, dude.

49:30.801 --> 49:31.885
We'll be all right.

49:32.928 --> 49:34.805
You got the place,
you get the bigger room.

49:35.097 --> 49:35.931
For now.

49:37.599 --> 49:40.894
Me and Joey had a talk one night
about my aftercare plan,

49:40.978 --> 49:44.064
and he said he thought
he was somewhat confident

49:44.731 --> 49:47.943
that I could live on my own
and probably be better off,

49:48.026 --> 49:50.487
not having to be
in a structured environment,

49:50.570 --> 49:52.364
as long as I had
a good support group, so...

49:52.823 --> 49:54.992
There's a really good community
of recovery here.

49:56.076 --> 49:58.120
I think that you'll fit right in, too.

50:05.002 --> 50:07.170
This is it, man. It's gonna be nice.

50:07.713 --> 50:10.799
Yeah, it's already nice.

50:31.403 --> 50:32.237
Oh, God.

50:32.320 --> 50:34.906
You look like a totally different person.
You look great.

50:35.323 --> 50:39.036
All right, acceptable, responsible
and productive.

51:18.241 --> 51:21.286
I don't wanna get out of bed.

51:25.540 --> 51:27.375
I gotta go pee in a cup.

51:29.628 --> 51:30.796
Story of my life.

51:31.588 --> 51:33.256
You piss in cups all day.

51:33.548 --> 51:34.841
I have to pee in a cup.

51:34.925 --> 51:38.220
I've heard rumors.
It was about Jeff drinking.

51:39.137 --> 51:41.890
Chad told me
that he had been out one night,

51:41.973 --> 51:43.642
and he had given him a breathalyzer,

51:43.725 --> 51:46.520
and it had come back
a little bit positive kind of.

51:47.312 --> 51:48.396
He wasn't sure,

51:48.480 --> 51:50.982
but Jeff claimed
he definitely didn't drink.

51:52.734 --> 51:55.695
Chad called me and said,
"Everybody's worried about your recovery,"

51:55.779 --> 51:56.780
and I said, "Why?"

51:57.489 --> 52:00.117
He said, "You're hanging back out
with your family a lot."

52:00.575 --> 52:02.661
And I'm like, "I ain't gonna stop.

52:03.286 --> 52:05.622
Why would I stop
'cause you told me to stop?"

52:06.206 --> 52:09.000
I've been drug tested 18 fucking times
since I've been up there,

52:09.459 --> 52:10.919
not even up there two months.

52:11.586 --> 52:14.089
Probably breathalyzed ten times.
It's like...

52:15.132 --> 52:18.510
And no one else in that whole place
up there gets that shit.

52:19.010 --> 52:20.595
It's just me for some odd reason.

52:20.679 --> 52:24.224
They think 'cause I'm hanging out
with my sister, I'm gonna use. You know?

52:26.268 --> 52:28.270
Man, if I want to use, I will go use.

52:28.353 --> 52:29.896
If I want to drink, I'll go drink.

52:29.980 --> 52:31.189
I choose not to, so...

52:32.357 --> 52:34.359
I got more important things
to worry about.

52:34.442 --> 52:37.362
I freaking worry about my kids.
I work, you know?

52:37.445 --> 52:40.448
It's like, I'm doing everything right,
leave me the fuck be.

52:42.117 --> 52:43.326
But they just don't.

53:25.410 --> 53:26.703
What's going on, Jeff?

53:29.331 --> 53:30.916
I have no clue what's going on.

53:35.795 --> 53:37.714
I don't know what's gonna happen, man.

53:39.049 --> 53:41.718
This place is turning into
a fucking shit show.

53:42.719 --> 53:45.680
Everybody fucked up,
covering for each other,

53:46.723 --> 53:48.099
drinking in the house.

53:49.684 --> 53:51.269
Doing dumb shit, man.

53:54.147 --> 53:57.234
I've been drinking. Got caught.

53:58.235 --> 54:00.487
So I don't know what's happening,

54:00.570 --> 54:03.323
but the word on the street is that
they're shutting this place down.

54:04.282 --> 54:05.116
So...

54:11.748 --> 54:13.583
to figure it out. I'm not sure.

54:13.667 --> 54:16.336
-Craig, you're just in time, man.
-Yeah? For what?

54:16.628 --> 54:19.005
We're trying to hammer this thing out.

54:19.631 --> 54:24.302
So what Jeff told Chad and I was
that he was at a girl's house.

54:24.386 --> 54:26.763
He was coming home
in the wee hours of the morning,

54:26.846 --> 54:32.227
ran off the road, hit this person's house
and then backed up, left the scene.

54:33.353 --> 54:35.397
Unambiguously, he has relapsed.

54:36.314 --> 54:39.192
And other people confirming
that this has been daily.

54:39.651 --> 54:43.029
I think we could bring him back in here
and help him.

54:44.030 --> 54:44.864
What do you think?

54:45.740 --> 54:48.493
I don't think you can bring all of them
in this residence,

54:48.576 --> 54:51.997
now that they've created
a triad of use and...

54:54.791 --> 54:55.834
enabling.

54:56.376 --> 54:58.712
I think Jeff needs a higher level of care.

54:59.045 --> 55:01.339
the kids.

55:01.756 --> 55:03.633
He's at a legal point,

55:03.717 --> 55:06.219
where if he doesn't get them
in the next 30 days,

55:06.344 --> 55:09.639
he doesn't get another shot at 'em.
He loses them permanently.

55:09.723 --> 55:12.767
That's my biggest fear is
if we sit down with Jeff and say,

55:12.851 --> 55:16.313
"Here's your only course of action,"

55:17.147 --> 55:20.025
he knows what that means,
and he knows,

55:20.483 --> 55:23.445
"I'll never get my girls back,"
and I think at that moment,

55:23.528 --> 55:24.988
we just say goodbye to Jeff.

55:25.071 --> 55:27.866
I think he's shooting up tomorrow
and dead in a week.

55:28.867 --> 55:32.203
That is a very realistic scenario here.

55:32.287 --> 55:35.957
The other part of that is
you put these girls in his hands...

55:36.041 --> 55:38.209
- I know.
- ...they're going to be dead, too.

55:38.543 --> 55:41.046
You're not looking... You gotta...

55:41.129 --> 55:46.634
We're looking at a menu
of shitty decisions and options,

55:46.718 --> 55:48.720
and not one of them is right.

55:49.429 --> 55:52.891
One of them has to be made,
but not one of them is good.

56:06.029 --> 56:08.615
All right, boys.
Come out wherever you are.

56:10.492 --> 56:14.788
I apologize to you guys
that I wasn't insightful enough

56:14.871 --> 56:16.873
to know this wasn't a good idea for you.

56:17.248 --> 56:19.793
I thought that even though
this wasn't finished,

56:19.876 --> 56:21.920
and it wasn't ready,
and we didn't have a manager,

56:22.295 --> 56:24.506
I thought that you guys had come so far,

56:24.589 --> 56:28.051
that this was going to work out
until we got it finished.

56:28.176 --> 56:31.012
So, you guys were at a disadvantage.

56:31.304 --> 56:34.391
Having said that,
you guys also fucked up.

56:35.433 --> 56:38.728
So we all share some responsibility
in what's going on here.

56:39.729 --> 56:43.566
We've got to figure out how can we make
you guys safe in your recovery.

56:44.109 --> 56:45.735
This place is obviously not it.

56:46.903 --> 56:49.572
So that leaves us with,
what are we gonna do next?

56:50.240 --> 56:53.243
Adam, I think, has already talked
with Craig about going to Minnesota

56:53.326 --> 56:55.286
and going to sober living out there,

56:55.370 --> 56:58.248
and I think that that would be
an appropriate option for him.

56:58.331 --> 57:00.125
Is that a plan you're willing to engage?

57:00.208 --> 57:01.084
-Yeah.
-Good.

57:01.668 --> 57:06.297
All right, Rush,
we would like to throw this out at you.

57:07.048 --> 57:10.385
The opportunity for you
to re-enter Jacob's Ladder

57:11.219 --> 57:12.804
and to start at the bottom

57:13.346 --> 57:14.973
and work the program again,

57:15.056 --> 57:17.559
then start working on yourself over,

57:18.268 --> 57:19.769
if you'd like to do that.

57:20.145 --> 57:21.312
Honestly, I feel...

57:22.313 --> 57:24.732
I feel better than I have been
in the past couple of weeks

57:24.816 --> 57:26.568
'cause I don't have to lie
about it anymore.

57:27.318 --> 57:31.197
I've never, ever stuck with it
and sat here through the consequences.

57:31.698 --> 57:33.199
I've always gone.

57:33.867 --> 57:35.869
I had money in my pocket, I still do,

57:36.244 --> 57:38.163
and my first instinct was to run.

57:38.371 --> 57:39.205
Yeah.

57:39.330 --> 57:42.000
But I didn't, and I think
that was a huge step for me.

57:42.083 --> 57:44.419
Like I told you yesterday,
I'm proud of you for that, man.

57:45.753 --> 57:47.172
That leaves us with Jeff.

57:50.049 --> 57:51.176
Yours is tough, man.

57:51.259 --> 57:52.427
Yours is tough because,

57:52.510 --> 57:57.474
honestly, the extent
of how far off track you went.

57:58.057 --> 58:00.101
I mean, it's the life you led before.

58:00.560 --> 58:02.979
The only difference is
you're not injecting yet.

58:03.438 --> 58:04.856
Breaking the law, lying,

58:05.356 --> 58:07.650
taking what you want when you want,
how you want.

58:08.735 --> 58:10.153
Your situation with your girls.

58:10.236 --> 58:14.741
I've already called Kristen Antolini,
and I asked her, "Is there any leeway?"

58:15.492 --> 58:16.743
She has to talk to the judge,

58:16.826 --> 58:20.455
but she thinks you could have
until mid-to-late January

58:21.247 --> 58:23.374
to stretch this out
and get yourself some help.

58:24.042 --> 58:26.127
Question is,
where are you going to get that help?

58:26.836 --> 58:28.087
What do you want, Jeff?

58:28.421 --> 58:29.255
Nothing.

58:30.131 --> 58:31.382
No help with us?

58:31.466 --> 58:33.801
-No help...
-I'm already fucked, dude.

58:35.178 --> 58:36.596
I just want my girls, dude.

58:37.305 --> 58:39.891
Drinking, you know what I mean,
fucked it all up.

58:40.808 --> 58:42.185
Now I ain't gonna get 'em.

58:43.811 --> 58:45.563
By the time I go there and get out,

58:46.105 --> 58:48.441
I ain't had no time to get on my feet,
get 'em home.

58:48.525 --> 58:49.943
It'll be over with, anyways.

58:50.527 --> 58:52.570
So I'm basically fucked all around,

58:53.238 --> 58:55.156
because I chose to drink a little bit.

